==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|growen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|grōwan||to grow, increase, flourish, germinate}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*grōaną||to grow, grow green}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*gʰreh₁-||to grow, become green}}.
{{rel-top|cognates}}
Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|grow|lang=sco}}, {{term|grew||to grow|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|grojen|lang=frr}}, {{term|growen||to grow|lang=frr}}, {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|groeie||to grow|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|groeien||to grow|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|grüejen||to grow, grow green|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|gro||to grow|lang=da}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|gro||to grow|lang=no}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|gro||to germinate, grow, sprout|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|gróa||to grow|lang=is}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|herba||plant, herb, weed|lang=la}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|gröda||crop|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|frr|-}} {{term|greyde||growth, pasture|lang=frr}}. Related to [[growth]], [[grass]], [[green]].
